text:
52nd Street, corner Lexington to Park Avenue.
(Before Reconstruction):
President Borough of Manhattan.
November 21, 1921.

52nd St Lexington Avenue to Park Avenue,
(Before Reconstruction)
President Borough of Manhattan. CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE.  November 21, 1921.

(1)
Swedish Methodist Episcopal Church, Lexington Ave., at the S.W.
corner of 52nd Street.
May 3, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing the 52nd Street side. Story of church in:
"New York Times" January, 29, 1937, page 38.
January 24, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
Similar to No. 1, but more extensive northward. Note the 1-story business and theatre building that is replacing the Church. North of
same is the Y.w.C.A.
October 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
